<p align="center"><font size="7">Using the Face Alive Features</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">To use the Face Alive features you must first 
access the &quot;Face Alive&quot; tab.</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">1. Click &quot;Face Alive&quot; tab</font></p>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="page_611.jpg" width="810" height="810"></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">2. You now have the ability to change the default 
location and port number of the Image Server, as well as the ability change the 
emoticons you use to represent yourself in the virtual classroom. You may change 
your emoticons at any time, whether you are connected to the image server or 
not. However, you can only upload your updated emoticons when connected to the 
image server.</font></p>
